{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike prior experiments using only instruction-tuning, this section explores post-pretraining, where a pretrained model undergoes additional pretraining before fine-tuning.",
    "The goal is to assess whether a pretrained or instructiontuned model as the expert is more effective and if post-pretraining adds value or instruction-tuning alone is sufficient for MoFE models.",
    "For testing in the medical domain, the pretraining datasets include English data from the Multilingual-Medical-Corpus (García-Ferrero et al., 2024) for the medical domain and Multi-News data (Fabbri et al., 2019) for the general domain.",
    "Due to dataset distribution balance, a random sample of 0.2 million rows from each dataset, totaling 0.4 million rows, is used for training.",
    "The MedMCQA instruction dataset is used for instruction-tuning across all strategies."
  ]
}